%% AutomationOS Context Switch Sequence
%% Mermaid Sequence Diagram

sequenceDiagram
    participant Timer as Timer IRQ<br/>(PIT @ 1000 Hz)
    participant IDT as IDT Handler<br/>(interrupt.asm)
    participant Sched as Scheduler<br/>(scheduler.c)
    participant ProcA as Process A<br/>(current)
    participant Switch as context_switch()<br/>(context_switch.asm)
    participant ProcB as Process B<br/>(next)

    Note over Timer,ProcB: Timer tick occurs (every 1ms)

    Timer->>IDT: IRQ 0 (Timer interrupt)
    activate IDT
    Note over IDT: Hardware:<br/>• Push RIP, CS, RFLAGS<br/>• Push error code<br/>• Jump to ISR

    IDT->>IDT: Save registers<br/>(push all GPRs)

    IDT->>Sched: schedule()
    activate Sched

    Sched->>Sched: Decrement time_slice<br/>of current process

    alt Time slice expired
        Note over Sched: Process A's time slice = 0

        Sched->>Sched: scheduler_pick_next()
        Note over Sched: Round-robin selection:<br/>1. Find next READY process<br/>2. Skip BLOCKED processes<br/>3. Wrap around to queue start

        Sched->>ProcA: Get current process
        activate ProcA
        ProcA-->>Sched: Process A (state=RUNNING)
        deactivate ProcA

        Sched->>ProcB: Get next process
        activate ProcB
        ProcB-->>Sched: Process B (state=READY)

        Sched->>Sched: Update states:<br/>• A: RUNNING → READY<br/>• B: READY → RUNNING

        Sched->>Switch: context_switch(A, B)
        activate Switch

        Note over Switch: Save Process A context:
        Switch->>ProcA: Save to A->context:<br/>• RAX, RBX, RCX, RDX<br/>• RSI, RDI, RBP, RSP<br/>• R8-R15<br/>• RIP, RFLAGS<br/>• CR3 (page table)

        Note over Switch: Load Process B context:
        Switch->>ProcB: Load from B->context:<br/>• Restore all registers<br/>• Load CR3 (switch address space)<br/>• Update TSS RSP0<br/>(kernel stack)

        Switch->>Switch: Switch stacks:<br/>RSP ← B->kernel_stack

        Switch-->>Sched: Context switch complete
        deactivate Switch
        deactivate ProcB

        Sched->>Sched: Update current_process = B

    else Time slice remaining
        Note over Sched: Process A continues running
    end

    Sched-->>IDT: Return from schedule()
    deactivate Sched

    IDT->>IDT: Restore registers<br/>(pop all GPRs)

    IDT->>IDT: Send EOI to PIC<br/>(End of Interrupt)

    IDT-->>ProcB: iretq (return from interrupt)
    deactivate IDT

    Note over ProcB: Process B now running<br/>on its own stack and address space

    Note over Timer,ProcB: Context switch overhead:<br/>~1000-2000 cycles (~0.5-1 μs)<br/>• Register save/restore: ~200 cycles<br/>• CR3 flush (TLB): ~500-1000 cycles<br/>• Scheduler logic: ~300-500 cycles
